Always wanted to taste true Cajun cuisine and my chance finally came when had a business day in New Orleans and at only a 100m from the hotel Galliano Restaurant was a God blessing. Friendly bar atmosphere, an inspiring menu and tasty food that felt like home cooked. I liked the Gumbo and the Shrimp n'Gritts, and the Fried Pudding was a nice culinary surprise. I definitely recommend to try a meal at Galliano.

Passing through NO, and staying locally.  Restaurant was empty, which is a sad by-product of COVID and hurricane season we understand.  We were warmly greeted by Amy, our very helpful and knowledgeable server.  We enjoyed the oyster in garlic starters that were wonderful.  The Gumbo was excellent ... there is a full crab and yes, there is a lot of meat on that crab, all for a very modest price.  Charley and Amy made us feel at home and the service was great.  We hope more folks will come down and enjoy the great food and service.

This restaurant was absolutely terrible. Between the five of us in our party our food came out to over 200$. Three out of five of the entrees ordered were hamburgers and all three of them came out blackened and burnt. The fourth entree was a extremely dry and disgusting short rib, which only came with two small pieces of meat for an absolutely outrageous price considering the quality of the meat. Our fifth entree was a crawfish and aligator fettuccine, which was just okay tasting but not at all worth the 40$ after added crab meat.  Our server was not very good, she took care of us okay when we were the only table in the restaurant. However 10 minutes after we sat down anotber group came in who apparently knew her personally and from then on out the service took a serious drop. To start the meal she asked if we would like to start with some water, to which we all said yes considering the heat and humidity in New Orleans. What she failed to mention was that the waters she gave us were 5$ per bottle, then continued to bring more bottles to the table and continued to fill our glasses without our consent or desire.  The restaurant could also use with some serious deep cleaning. The tables, plates, and cutlery were clean but the floors were definitely not. Walking on the floors you could feel how sticky and disgusting they were without even looking. There was also an unmistakable odor in the restaurant that we couldn't identify.  All in all this was easily the most disappointing food we have eaten in the week we have been here. Do yourself a favor and get fast food before going to Galliano restaurant.  Terrible food, very overpriced, and unclean restaurant. If I could rate 0 stars I would.

It was like eating canned green beans with the taste of liquid smoke. That dish I would avoid. Fortunately, the rest of the food and experience made up for it. I would definitely eat their again.

Fantastic laid back place with outstanding food and service.  Came highly recommended from a couple locals, and it is convenient to the convention center and Riverwalk.  Great place to entertain customers. Service was prompt and friendly. Local beers only, huge wine list. Food was exceptional.  We shared chargrilled oysters.  I had the Cajun Tournedos - 2 bacon wrapped filets with mashed potatoes and sautéed southern greens.  It was delicious.  The others in the party had the seafood platter and the blackened catch of the day.  They both enjoyed theirs. Prices were reasonable.  Service and atmosphere were excellent.  Will definitely return.

Went the last night we were in NOLA. Wanted something within walking distance from the hotel. We were exhausted from the week and just wanted a good meal without a lot of effort. Wow. We were not disappointed. Small place; chill with a few tables and a long bar. Busy for a Monday night, given all of the things going on at the convention center (including our own). Thankfully, we didn't need a reservation to eat at the bar. Cody (hope I'm spelling his name right) made the night even better. He was full of energy and very attentive. I love it when people seem to really enjoy what they do and are especially good at it. Amazing service. We did raw oysters, drinks, meals (I had the seafood platter and he had the pot roast), and dessert (bread pudding). It was comfort food at its finest. Highly recommend it. Larger parties might want to be sure to reserve ahead of time in order to ensure getting a table.
This place has amazing food and service! If you are lucky enough to get served by Cody, he won't disappoint! The food was phenomenal! If you are visiting New Orleans hit up Galliano's.

I’ve been to NOLA 3 times and eaten at many $$ - $$$ restaurants. This is the second restaurant out of all those to make it into my “must repeat” list. (The other is Bon Ton Cafe.) Everything we ate at Galliano was excellent, and better than the $$$ the night before. We had raw oysters and gumbo to start. Seafood Platter and Blackened market fish. We tasted each others’ entrees and both were impressed by the flavors, texture and attention to detail. Great, friendly service. Definite repeat!

The restaurant is located near the convention center and is easy to find. We made reservation woth yelp and was propmpty seated on arrival. Staff was friendly and the restaurant wasn't noisy although they were full. We ordered the chargrilled oysters and you must try them if you go here. We ordered the crawfish pasta and the old world tournedos. The pasta was creamy and filled with crawfish and the tournedos were cooked perfectly and melted in your mouth.
Great soup du jour, blackened drum and wonderful cioppino.  Very prompt and attentive service.  Pricing points are slightly off, but don't let that stop you from trying this cool restaurant.

Was really excited to try this place as I read a lot of great reviews. We went in hoping to get a table and there was nothing available for the whole night it was all reservations which was a bummer. I didn’t read anywhere that you need reservations! We did find a table at the bar though so it worked out. My husband got the catfish and really enjoyed it, and I got a vegetable pasta. Mine was really good, until I found a piece of plastic in it. Mistakes happen, so I just let the waitress know and she got a new plate going. The new plate came out and everything was delicious. Really great staff as well!

Excellent food and excellent service. Gumbo, charbroiled oysters, fried chicken, smoked double pork chop....soo good! Easily one of my favorite restaurants in New Orleans. Chef Tom, Charlie Brown, Bartender’s Fernando and Julio, Mike....keep it up🤙

AMAZING service!! Cannot say enough! My family dined here for lunch with my 2 little boys (one who is 12 months old and very active). The staff there was so completely warm and did not seem annoyed with us taking up so much space (stroller, high chair, and all our stuff!) The chef even came out and said hello and personally cut him and my other son up some apples and was just overwhelmingly kind! The food came out hot, quick and was so delicious!!! The wedge salad had a great twist and the chargrilled oysters were amazing! And the wine list was fantastic. My dad got the beer flight which was great too. It was a perfect stop and highly recommend!! We will be back!

My second time here and it was just as good as the first. I loved the chargrilled oysters and their catfish creole. I tried a New Orleans cocktail called a “sazerac” and it was way too strong for me so I stuck with my old faithful margarita, which was also strong lol. The customer service was just as good as the first time. Galliano is a must for anyone visiting New Orleans.

Very friendly and attentive staff. The atmosphere is very chill. Everyone in our party of 7 enjoyed their entrees. The fried alligator appetizer was cooked perfectly and still tender in texture. This is the first time I have tried fried alligator where it was not tough and chewy. Seafood Gumbo was good, but the catfish with shrimp creole was amazing. The catfish was crispy and light and the creole was rich and hearty. We enjoyed our evening and hope to return to try other items!

Showed up at 20:00hrs on a Saturday, about 10 open tables inside. Had a party of two and were told that it was a 2 hour wait without a reservation. Group of 6 comes in behind us, says they don’t have a reservation, and seated immediately.

Excellent for what it is. Atmosphere is casual, which is what we are after. Food was so good we had to visit again the next night. Recommend the side of Jambalaya. Pork chop is out of this world. Pay a visit. Best spot in the up and coming warehouse area.
Very good meal, server was pretty cool. Had duck wings, catfish, and courvoisier. Hands down best meal I had in a long time
Delicious blackened mahi mahi, and a terrific spinach salad. The service was outstanding as well. Fun mix of hits and Cajun music, and a large bar. Looking forward to going again!

Amazing meal complimented by some of the best service (ask for server Larry!!!) I have ever encountered. Seafood Coubion, Pork Chop La Place, Seafood Platter, Old World Tournedos, Chargrilled Oysters. All enjoyed.

Simply outstanding! Was in New Orleans for a conference and we had to go twice, after loving it so much the first time.  The owner (Richard, I think) was fantastic - very engaged with the customers and also cooking another night. Our server (Katy) was brilliant with us on both occasions and her recommendations were spot on.  Tried 3 mains: Cajun Prime Rib for 2, Southern Fried Chicken & Pork Chop la Place. All were amazing! Bring your appetite regardless of what you have, but especially for the prime rib! Appetizers and desserts were also lovely.  I could eat here every night! Make sure to check it out. I hope to be back in New Orleans one day to go again :-)

Excellent food and great service - we had the chicken fried filet minion and the seafood platter with bbq shrimp, drum, crawfish bread - all excellent and so full of great creole flavor. Great service too- we will be back!
Seafood platter was absolutely fantastic! Great service, relaxed atmosphere. Definitely recommend.
Delicious! Excellent service. Everyone in our group had something different, and everyone raved about their meal.
Great food, service and nice atmosphere.

Food was excellent. We had fried shrimp and mash potatoes. It was 25 dollar a plate. Which is too much for what we got. My nephew had to pay 90 dollars for their 2 plates and one plate to split with kids.  They don't put prices on their menus so we was a little shocked.
Seafood platter was super fantastic, dessert is a must!
Awesome food!!!
Love the sea food and music
Good.
All I can say is Great Place. Everything is delicious. Great staff. A lil pricey but well worth it.

WOW! AMAZING FOOD... TREMENDOUS SERVICE... WORTH THE WAIT! Dinner was great... I got red beans and bacon smothered greens! The best food overall that I had while visiting. I will be back when I come to town again.
Overrated! I don't recommend.

The food is expensive and the food is not good. Worst red beans and rice ever. Plus the hostess was rude. She asked if I had a reservation and looked at me all crazy. She showed me the menu to see if the prices almost to scare me away. I wish I would of ran. Over priced below average food. Two thumbs down. Stay away.
Amazzzzing food:)) And great service.
Good food, friendly staff.
The food was fabulous, and so was the service! Claire was at the bar, super friendly and personable and the food was equally as great! 10/10 recommend!
The sauce is fantastic!!!

As seems to be the case with new orleans, the outside of the restaurant does not preface the interior. My friend and I stumbled upon this gem in our quest to find Cajun food close to the convention center. We reached early enough that there was no wait or need for reservations. We got 2 appetizers and a main to split between us. The duck wings came recommended, while I wanted to try the alligator, so I chose the alligator sauce piquante appetizer. The main entre was a blackened salmon on a bed of veggies. The appetizers trumped everything! So so so good. The sauce for the duck wings was beyond fantastic. I actually dipped salmon in it, while my friend scraped the remains off the plate. The alligator meat was fried, savory, the sauce spicy. The salmon was just as expected- blackened and crisp on the outside and melting soft on the inside.  The complimentary hush puppies were great too! All in all, great experience, cute little restaurant and recommend it to any travellers to NOLA!
Great cajun food with a flair. Huge portions.

Attentive server, delicious food, and reasonably priced in a very relaxed atmosphere. Had the chicken and sausage gumbo and the appetizer (could be an entree) Boudin with collard greens and chow chow. Both items were well seasoned and beautifully presented. Highly recommended.
Small little town vibe but the people are vibrant and friendly.  Amazing food Shrimp Crawfish Jambalaya.  People seeking jobs offshore this the place to come
Great food with the original Lousiana style
Excellent

For my last meal on my second vacation to New Orleans I went to Galliano and man was it worth it. I got the chicken fried filet steak and it was to die for. I ended the night with the chocolate chip bread pudding and it was one of my favorite desserts to date. The environment is friendly and the restaurant is beautiful. Highly recommend!
The staff here was super friendly and the food was excellent!
They have one of the best shrimps I have ever tasted. I also like the idea that the owner is around to check on their guests. I would definitely come back here.
Yummy! Oysters!

Excellent food.  Went there with a group of 8 people.  Of the 8 dishes, apps and drinks only one dish was so-so, the rest were amazing. The collard greens were quite possibly some of the best I have ever had. The service was fine to good, did not take away from the meal or really enhance it either.  Overall highly recommend it, it was a great place.  The food really spoke for itself.  Looking at other tables, everyone seemed to be enjoying their food and everything looked very enjoyable to eat.

I ran across Galliano while looking for a bite to eat. Outside the door was a sign advertising their happy hour from 3-5 p.m.  I ordered two bowls of the chicken and sausage gumbo and a drink. For less than $15 I got a delicious midday lunch.  Also, one of the employees was shucking oysters right there at the bar, which I'd never seen in person before. He let me know how he prepares the oyster so it doesn't have any sand in it.  Overall, very satisfied with the service, food, and quality of my dining. I'd recommend this to anyone who wants a healthy and tasty meal at a very affordable price.

Went here for late night food. Had a good cocktail and enjoyed the alligator. The group of us split their oysters, tried both raw and chargrilled. Both were great. Only downside was the serve was a bit crass, but meant well.
Great find. Casual dining, awesome food. My wife ordered the fried chicken - it was probably the best fried chicked either of us ever ate. I had the porkchop - it too was awesome. Portions were huge.
Absolutely fantastic! Save room for the bread pudding
Wasn't feeling the vibe with the waitor.  Food was good.
Amazing grill oysters! I don't even like oysters but love these! Would have preferred softer bread to go with my meal but otherwise it was tasty
I'm not a shellfish eater. The free range stuffed chicken breast was excellent. The rest of the party enjoyed their shellfish, too.
The food is awesome!! Make sure you try the raw oysters, they are super fresh and super good! Great service, nice people

The food was not great, at all. But what was worse was the service. I made a reservation. Upon arrival they sat us at a table with our back very close to a crowded bar. I asked our server if we could be moved as there were at least 5 empty tables for 4 available. He immediately goes into "those are reserved for people who made a reservation." Ok. So with that, I went to the hostess. She started to say the same thing when I remind her that we have a reservation and point out the numerous empty tables. She says she will need to speak to her manager and as she does she huffs and rolls her eyes, hard. Oh I'm so sorry to annoy you. The manager, I regret not getting his name, was accommodating and understood why we wanted to move. He is the only reason we stayed after the previous service received. Again, although the portions are huge, it was quite bland. I wouldn't recommend or return when I'm back in New Orleans.
Food and service were excellent. Very clean and nice place.
Stopped in for a snack and cocktail.  Awesome fire roasted oysters.  Highly recommended
Pretty good food. We were told that the oysters were the best grown in the area. All of truly think Drago's were the best we have ever  had. Prime Rib was good but not great.
The pork chop was as good as they promised. Caution, it is HUGE. I wish I knew. I would have shared it with a family of 4.
Awesome food, awesome atmosphere and awesome staff. A win, win, win.
Everything about this place is awesome. Food was great, service was friendly and quick, and decor was charming <3 <3 <3
Fried Filet Mignon was recommended by the locals and were they ever right!!!
Special event meal! Fantastic quality, went with a group and everyone's dish looked awesome
Awesome food. Great comfort food, with native Cajun influence. Owner is hands on, staff & service is attentive. Highly recommend this restaurant. Best food so far!
Absolutely amazing... First trip to New Orleans and first stop. Couldn't ask for a better experience. Friendly workers and very attentive ... Definitely set the bar high
Excellent.
Casual atmosphere, and delicious food. Every dish we tried had a unique flavor. Our server, Josh,  couldn't have been better. Get here early, unless you have a reservation.

Wonderful service. Ended up ordering the duck for an app along with the gumbo. Both were absolutely to die for. The French bread was amazing. Seafood platter was our entree it wasn't your average "everything fried" seafood platter. The shrimp were great. I give this place all thumbs up! Ps you must try the apple cobbler. Jacque you were awesome!
The prime rib is amazing melts in your mouth.

Had dinner here while in New Orleans. There was a group of us and the staff was hospitable. They allowed us to celebrate and they were on the money with our food. I had the prime rib which I shared with a friend and it was perfect. The drinks were good also. No complaints. Our entire party was satisfied
Decent wine selection. The pork chop is fantastic.  Portion sizes are generous.  The deserts are amazing.  Great atmosphere!  We thoroughly enjoyed our evening.
Food was awesome!
Excellent, staff was super welcoming and kind. Felt right at home

The Louisiana shrimp was absolutely delicious and enjoyed the fried oysters! The gate was just okay, the batter on the gator wasn't as good as the shrimp.
One of the best meals we had during our stay in New Orleans!! Our waitress was awesome.  She helped us make our dinner and dessert choices and all 5 were excellent. I would definitely go back.
charbrioled oysters are not the best.   needs improvement.
The craw fish pasta was excellent. Was there at lunchtime and restaurant was empty and that's not surprising when one looks at the menu and prices. I recommend to go there for dinner.
Loved it. Had a Bloody Mary and seafood gumbo for an appetizer and a grilled platter for my entree. All was very good including the strawberry bread pudding for dessert.
Terrible service.
Little bit of a wait, but well worth it....

Fried chicken was perfect and fried shrimp also solid. Rougaroux mixed rum drink comes in a small fishbowl and only $5 at happy hour. Good service.
Very lively place. Good food and superb vibes. Char grilled oysters is must try.
Service was great. Just ordered wine and appetizers and soup, so can’t speak to the entree dishes. I would recommend the crab gratin and charbroiled oysters.

I was totally unimpressed with this place. It was not busy and we were treated as though it was a bother we were there.  I understand that this is all in a high tourist area but I asked our hotel for a reasonably priced place four a party of five to eat. I guess my concept of moderately priced differs from theirs.
Excellent food, drink and atmosphere

Let me just tell you one so far it has been one of the best food and experiences in all my travels from Australia to Mexico to San Francisco and sandiego. Very expensive but quality will match it. The bartender and manager serve you like they were your friends. One of them did their own personal open mic night with Joe rogan's jokes. They have two ribeye steaks prepared differently and boy they are good and then dessert pumpkin bread pudding and bourbon peacon pie.  And of course they have alcohol it's New Orleans. With a city with so much food to offer this has to be one if not the best. It is a must to have dinner here New Orleans. I hope they never change I plan to fly my whole family here just to have it.
Great atmosphere, fantastic waiter who really took time to explain the menu. Great food
Michael our waiter was fantastic!

When my husband and I travel together, we often ask, 'as this is our 1st time here in our travels, what is a 'not to be missed' offering from the menu?' The Duck Wings - meh. Amazing service. Definitely very knowledgeable about the menu and the different spices being used. Great recommendation on dinner and drinks. Also had oysters and they were very delicious.

Casual and comfortable establishment. Well prepared meals of good quality ingredients. Very nice gumbo and local style meals. Helpful and friendly staff. Near the convention center. Reasonable prices and good value.
Reasonable New Orleans fare...great staff...and check out this chocolate bread pudding...like a brownie with a smooth chewy texture

We ate here a few nights ago. Service was excellent. Contrary to a couple of reviews, I found the wine list to be pretty good. They were busy and noise was tolerable. I thought the food was very good. I had the double pork chop. Let me tell you, if you order that, have an appetite. You'll be in for a fight to the death. Delicious. My wife had the catfish and enjoyed it. No room for dessert, so can't help you. There have been some comments about the TV's. Wife and I like glancing at a game from time to time. In addition, they just didn't really seem obtrusive. The bar looked like a nice place to hang out. Prices quite reasonable for the area.
The chicken that was marinated for 24 hour wasn't that great. One of my pieces of chicken wasn't done. The service and staff are great.

Nice atmosphere, service was very good.  The house salad was excellent.  The shrimp poboy was meh.....a lot of bread and not very much shrimp - did not even cover the sandwich.

Great atmosphere,  staff is incredibly welcoming.  The food...... amazing, my fiance and I were truly taken back. We got the alligator app, then fried catfish and a shrimp Po' Boy. Everything was perfectly seasoned and the sauces were outstanding.  We're here for a week and this is the first place we tried, the problem is I want to try a bunch of places but I'm afraid I'll just want to keep coming back here. Plus they have a huge drink menu with local beers. Oh, and they play great music. If you're in NOLA, this place is a must.
Service and food was very good, we had the ribeye for two. It did get a little noisy near the end of the evening, but a great Neighborhood Restaurant.

We made reservations for 7:30pm but arrived 30min early and were seated immediately on a Thursday night. They were busy so I reccomend making a reservation. The atmosphere was very relaxed and not "stuffy". Our waiter Paul was excellent. We had the popcorn chicken and alligator bites appetizers, both very good. I had the Sangria and my sister had the Moscow mule, both delicious. I had the special,  Lamb, mashed potatoes and fried shrimp. It was excellent.  Everyone in our party of 4 liked everything they ordered as well. Would definitely go back.

amazing catfish

This is our first time in NOLA. Someone told us to go to Mulate's but the reviews here were amazing. And OMG the reviews don't give it justice. The atmosphere is chill, the people are super polite, and the owner came around and told us one of the secret ingredients in the collard greens. Our server was Larry and he was outstanding. He was polite, genuine, and had good conversation. This place is gets 5 star and A+. We will definitely be back next time we are in NOLA!
Service was wonderful and the chargrilled oysters were perfect. So good I wanted to lick the shells! We also loved the corn and chowder soup. Will definitely be back!
Great service along with amazing food! Definitely a must to come back and eat.
Attentive service and tasty food. A must repeat when in town.

Great food and very attentive service. Ate here one night and came back after eating elsewhere to sample more of their menu. The portuons are generous; my wife and shared appetizers and entrees both meals.  The char grilled oysters were definitely tastier than Dragos (where we also ate).  Catfish and Pork Chop (pictured) earned high marks, along with the gumbo and chowder. Unlike the other restaraunts recommended, it had the feel of a local hangout. Service was casual and friendly while also very attentive and knowledgeable about the offerings on the menu. While certainly convenient to the warehouse district hotels and convention center, Galliano is worth the walk from the French Quarter for a great meal.
A chill and delicious middle ground between the deep fried tourist traps like mulate's and the uber pretentious hipster joints in the warehouse district. Great food, staff, and atmosphere.
Tried the double stack pork chop one of their praised dish and unfortunately my meal wasnt cooked well. The owner was nice and apologetic taking half off the meal. Worth a 2nd try!
Excellent food and service. Loved the Shrimps with grits and the Crawfish w linguini.

Food was ok. Service was not what I would expect. It seemed that the waiter was new and easily confused. We had to ask for little touches that you normally get, like the cloth to clean up after eating seafood with our hands.  It was also very loud, but I'll probably give it another try when I'm back in town
great service and good food
Loved it, tasted fresh and deliciously seasoned! Great place to east if you're at the convention center and need a sitdown getaway.
Good oysters!!!
Great food and service.  Bartenders and servers were friendly, food was outstanding.
Try the shrimp and grits appetizer.   Delicious!
Best oysters I ever had and everything else was awesome too
Wonderful food and drinks
Great food

This food at this restaurant was great, and so was our waitress...until. Until we received our bill, which we split down the middle between two people, that coincidentally had $11 added to each check. The receipt did not state gratuity could be added as LA that is illegal.  Our pleasant waitress had convenienlty stepped out, so another assisted us and did not care to give us an explanation or even suggest what could've happened. Unacceptable. The manager did not come over to apologize, nor have the waitress when she came back in (without making eye contact) explain what may have cause the overcharge. Unacceptable.  We were great customers and happen to tip very well everywhere we go...and STILL Tipped her well because she was a great waitress. We felt discriminated against as we were the only people of color at the time being served. UNACCEPTABLE.  The food is great, but check your bill...especially if you happen to be out of town.  ---REPLY TO OWNER--- Thank you for your reply. I would like to be clear, we DID NOT ask for separate checks, instead Wanda asked us if we wanted the check split and we declined separate checks. We preferred to split the one bill down the middle which all point of sales systems allow as I am an analyst for one.  I appreciate this response, however, it would have been more appreciated had that apology and simple explanation come from Wanda or Charlie (assuming he was the manager that night).  They both avoided eye contact as we sat boxing our food- I even saw Charlie look out the corner of his eye. No apology. No explanation. No "have a good night". Unacceptable!  This review is solely based on their cold treatment toward us, that could have simply ended with, "it was a mistake and we're sorry..." We would have accepted that because she was simply that sweet of a waitress, but to then completely ignore us while we watched her colleague explain to her what happened and continued to ignore us.  It should have been just as easy to tell us in person as it was to reply here that it was a long day, and a simple miscalculation. If you can't tell, the 180 degree switch in our treatment was blatant and left us believing the overcharge was intentional, otherwise a genuine apology would have been immediate. The food is great but I will be filing with the better business bureau as service and management to treat customers in that way is abusive and should not be directed to others.
good food, small portions, long waiting time
Staff very friendly, good food
The food was really good and the drinks were pretty strong. I tried red beans and rice at three places and theirs was the best.  I would definitely try again.
this was a nice experience.  food was good.  grits were a little gritty but i think thats how they eat them here.  id love to eat here again.
Amazing place. The staff is very helpful. Try the duck hot wings!

First visit. Took friends visiting from out of town. As a local, very happy to have Galliano in my neighborhood. Their seafood is the real deal and staff was spot on. An all around solid experience.

The food is pretty good, nothing to write home about. The service definitely leaves more to be desired. I waited at least ten minutes before getting water, and slow service followed suit thereafter. The prices do not match the food or the service, if they're going to charge a lot for food, the experience should be on pat. The atmosphere is nice and rustic, and the food is decent. A solid 3/5 establishment.
Sat for 15 minutes no service.....

Appetizers were good, but the deep fried filet mignon had no flavor and the steak was so thin it was unnoticeable in several bites.  I would not get it again if I ever go back.  Sadly, the side of beans were much better and more flavorful than the steak.

I had an outstanding lunch here - it was a short walk from the convention center, and the service and food were both excellent. I had their oyster po' boy and a side of jambalaya - the jambalaya was tasty if a little less spicy than I'd hoped, and the po' boy was the best I've had in New Orleans. That combined with a pleasant atmosphere and friendly, responsive service made this a great experience - next time I'm at a convention in New Orleans, this will be my designated lunch spot. :-)
Loved It! Great food and great service!

Great food, great service, great atmosphere.  We had he grilled oysters as an appetizer and they were better than Acme Ouster House - my former favorite.  For entrees the southern fried chicken and Cajun pasta Monica were outstanding. My …

Delicious but pretty heavy. I got the fried catfish, which was a pretty big portion of 2 filets. Also, the server offered still or sparkling water but neglected to mention that sparkling will cost extra so just be aware.
The best oysters on the half shell in town. Service was amazing. Will eat there again upon my return visit to New Orleans

Amazing food! Out of the 6 days in New Orleans this was by far our best meal and service! We asked Brett our waiter to order us a 3 course meal. He nailed it! The chowder, gumbo, oysters and crawfish pasta were all so good!
Great local style food with a creative twist. Definitely have to try their char grilled oysters.
Delicious food, great service.
Terry was the best bartender! We got the prime rib for two and it was HUGE but delicious!! Happy Hour in weekdays from 5:30-6:30 with drink and oyster specials.
The place to go for New Orleans Flavor!!
Great food in a casual atmosphere at a decent price. We experienced great service as well.

Wonderful experience dining here. Came by myself for dinner and ended up with a fabulous meal, a full belly and a few new friends! The bartender was amazingly helpful and helped me navigate my entire dining experience. I tried new things and enjoyed every bite! Tried the char grilled oysters, she crab soup and pasta Monica! My inner fat child is doing a happy dance! 😂
Make sure to make reservations!
Enjoyed the food here. Server was awesome, kept is in drinks, and had suggestions to us as first timers that were spot on. The oysters were worth fighting over.
Never ever again!! While eating I found a piece of aluminum in my food. When I brought it to the managers attention I was informed that I was eating a piece of the dish scrubber.

Excellent food 😋  Elle and Charlie( waiter & waitress) were excellent. Little girl at front desk seemed a little young to be worker there ( 13 yrs old) while making soft drinks 🍹.  Anyways the service was amazing 😉
We ate at the Galliano while visiting New Orleans it's was awesome we were there twice our waiter and waitress were awesome also highly recommend!!
Great food, great service and great atmosphere! The Seafood Platter is excellent!
A-plus all around! Great service, cocktails, and food. We had a large group and they were extremely accommodating and everyone loved what they ordered!!
Great food and drinks. Sat at the bar and the bartender and oyster guy were very personable
Great spot for a quick lunch. Great Cajun options. Usually packed.
Went here for lunch with some coworkers.  I would say it was a little pricey for lunch, but the PO-Boy was amazing!  Only try the Bloody Mary if you like hot stuff.  It was spicy, but delicious.

Took my wife out for a nice evening to this place which was recommended to us.  The waiter kept asking my wife if she wanted another Diet Coke even though she had a regular coke.  The food was over cooked and overrated.  They tried to rush us out by bringing the check before we ever finished eating our food.  We had to ask to see the desert menu and the waiter acted bothered to have to go get it.  We have 5 kids and don’t get to have to many romantic diners out so it’s really disappointing when we do and the restaurant sucks.  My advice, don’t waste your time or money here.

I was pleasantly surprised by our meal here. The best red beans and collards I've had, and really tasty fried chicken. Charbroiled oysters were BOMB - a little pricier than you'll find further from the quarter but worth it (fresh oysters are $1 each at happy hour and charbroiled are 6 for $10 or 12 for $20). Left full and happy.  The place was empty when we arrived at 5:30 but by 6 it was pretty much full. Recommend a 5:30 reservation for the best service.
Chargrilled oysters a must. Whats better than a filet or a country fried steak? How about a country fries filet!

Holy cow is their gumbo amazing! My wife had that and the bacon wrapped filet, which was also on point. I had the fried catfish and that was very delicious as well. We finished off the dinner with a wonderful white chocolate bread pudding and I can honestly say it was the best dinner we had all week in New Orleans.
Top notch food in a low key environment 1 block from convention center.
Great food. Great service.
Wonderful, sublime, busy, caloric, charming.
Great authentic southern food and great service.
Outstanding! A mandatory stop when you come to New Orleans
Best meal in nola
Good food. Fast, efficient and friendly.

This place is amazing! Gritty with a down home feel, I presumed a lot of locals come here. The staff were great, from the host to the bartender, the server to the "oyster shucker" as it said on his hat, everybody has each other's backs. I think this is important in making patrons feel welcome, which I sure did. I had a beer flight of local brews, and the seafood platter. Sooo delicious. Dessert was a tough decision, but I went with the white chocolate bread pudding. Again, phenomenal. I will be back!
Very Busy! Great food, and service but they were a little overwhelmed
Great atmosphere! The corn chowder with crab meat and sausage is delish!

Super friendly workers and delicious food. It's located right by the boardwalk and convention center.  They have a good selection of whiskey and other liquor. I got grilled and raw oysters, which were very good. I also good the gumbo, which was delicious. I'd definitely recommend this place
Excellent food. Even as as a big NYC seafood guy, these were the best oysters I've ever had. And the shucker taught us a bit about oyster farming!

The food here was amazing. We were a group of 9 here for Wrestlemania and ordered a variety of food. It was all so good, I regret ordering the Filet Mignon because every other dish was better! Not often you can say that. Definitely a must visit. Try the gator and pork chop. Amazing.
Food was good... that's it.
Great oysters. Super friendly staff. Good food.
Amazing food and service
Oh my...she crab chowder with corn and potatoes.  Wonderful red beans and rice with andouille sausage and ham hocks.  Talk about a variety of tastes.  Lovely bar,, good service.
Service was slow and not extremely friendly. Wasn't the cleanest or coziest establishment. Fried chicken was delicious and made up for it.
Lunch for 1 with 2 mixed drinks, appetizer, entry and dessert was $75. But it was very good.
Great local restaurant. Red beans and rice were delicious.

The Prime Rib for 2 is to die for!  I about died trying to finish it.  The greens were very flavorful.  The mashed potatoes needed a little help, but the prime rib was the awesome.    Medium was the mark as the cut is really thick.  Also, their Rougaleaux drink was a nice twist on the Hurricane.
Alligators for starters!  Fine gumbo; really tender meats.  And SO close to the Convention Center.  I'll go back next time I'll be in the exciting Big Easy.

Richard and his team gave us a warm southern welcome! They gave us sensational dishes to try! From the greens to the gumbo to the hush puppies! All tasty! As well as a great beer and adult beverage selection! Me and my folks were all pleased with the food, beverages, and service! Very fast and sharp! The folks there know what they're doing! I def plan to come again!
Pretty good food.
Great food and friendly staff. I came here from the conference center for dinner. I enjoyed a great meal, coubullion, and drinks.
The food and service was great. Although we arrived just 20 minutes before closing, they we gracious with their service.
Tasty and fancy food but casual dress.
Good great but the IPA keg was empty.

I came here on a busy lunch time. I had to wait for 10 min to get a seat. There was no wait list and no one directed me to my seat when it got empty. The food was good. I had raw oysters which were fresh and catfish creole which was nice too (I loved the sauce). I would've liked to give 5 stars but the service quality was not there.
Nice food, get a taste of Louisiana with the flavour of New Orleans. Friendly servers and nice happening crowd. Great to enjoy with group or even just sit on the bar.
meh....
Great lunch. Oysters were delicious
Good food and services

This place is awesome!! We walked in here at 3pm and they were closed but they were very polite and gave us another recommendation. Because they were so nice we decided to come back for dinner and made a reservation for 9:30pm. It was really worth coming back!! The food is good and services very nice.
chargrilled oysters were the Bomb!
Amazing food. Fabulous service. Beautiful atmosphere
They have the most creative drinks in town- balanced, unique and well flavored. The alligator appetizer is excellent but their corn chowder is absolutely the best I have ever tasted.

Wish we could have gotten back here. We ate here, the first night. Terry, our server and Doug, manager, were both friendly and helpful. I regret, we didn't get back for, the prime rib for two. We plan to come back! Promise! We came in, at the end of a very busy day. We had blackened fish, excellent and southern fried chicken. I wasn't happy with my chicken but wasn't making a big deal of it. Terry and Doug could tell and were nice enough to remove it and offered to replace it. I wasn't about to make the kitchen cook. I owned a restaurant, so I'm sympathetic, to days like they had. Impeccable service and attentive to customers needs. I thank you for your kindness. Hard to find that these days. Everything else was delicious. We will be back soon. Dying to try that prime rib.
Bone in rib eye is very good and almost too much for two. Friendly and attentive service. Nice place for a casual dinner.
Crawfish in my pasta was old and pastey. Other than that, best dessert I've had was the cobbler.
Best shrimp and grits I've ever eaten!
Best restaurant in New Orleans.  What a great meal.
